).We now divide the bar into three elements of length 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

.
 The total length of the bar is 
\begin_inset Formula $3h$
\end_inset

.
 From the analytic solution, we have: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u\left(y=h\right)=-\frac{2g}{3}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u\left(y=2h\right)=\frac{2g}{3}
\]

\end_inset

Since 
\begin_inset Formula $a=h+\epsilon h$
\end_inset

, we have:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u\left(y=a^{-}\right)=-g
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u\left(y=a^{+}\right)=g
\]

\end_inset

It is to note here that since the entire domain is of a single material
 and the jump in stress is zero, the solution will be symmetric and this
 is the same solution on applying a Dirichlet type of boundary condition
